                     <interp inst="t18280703-45-off233" type="offenceSubcategory" value="receiving"></interp>
               feloniously receiving of a certain evil disposed person, 1 cart, value 10l., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18280703-45-victim406" type="victimName">
                        James 
                        Deadman
                     <interp inst="t18280703-45-victim406" type="surname" value="Deadman"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280703-45-victim406" type="given" value="James"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280703-45-victim406" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280703-45-off233 t18280703-45-victim406"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , well knowing the same to have been stolen
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>MR. PHILLIPS conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>JAMES DEADMAN. On the 28th of December I entrusted John Hill, my servant, with a horse, cart, and harness, and he never returned; I saw my cart last Tuesday in possession of the prisoner - I knew it to be mine, by one wheel in particular; I asked him where he got it - he said, he bought it of a person who he named, and where he lived; that man is here - he said, he gave 4l. for it; I consider it worth 8l. or 10l., it cost me 18l. six months before.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. Was your name on it when you lost it? A. Yes; but when I found it the prisoner's name was on it - the prisoner told me at the public-house, that he would give it up, provided I did not take him before a Magistrate.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BODKIN. Q. Being a respectable tradesman he did not wish to go to the office? A. I believe his general character is good; he told me directly that he bought it of Doddridge - I took Doddridge before the Magistrate, and charged him as an accessary, or something; the Magistrate would not entertain the charge, because the thief could not be found.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280703-45-person407">
                  ROBINSON 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18280703-45-person407" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
